      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FOXFIRE EASTON NZ (6) enjoyed the class drop from the city last time out, coming from this barrier to score by 2.6 metres at Bathurst. Stays in the same grade and should be at peak fitness. Can strike again. MASTER GOUDA (9) enjoyed a drop in grade and a good draw when he led for an easy win at Albury last start, putting an impressive 11 metres on his nearest rival. Draws for a trail and the sprint lane is in play. GO COLOUR MY WORLD NZ (5) continued his good form when he came from the back row to miss by a nose last week. Scored back-to-back wins last month, one of them here. Major player. PIRANI PRINCESS (4) is worth thought after getting home by a head at this circuit and distance last week, giving her two wins and a placing from her last three starts.",
